            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Pat your<strong> rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then slice into strips and add to a large bowl with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!), <strong>cornflour</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>coated steak</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687507572361-x200.jpg",
